tweet: 14/ Enabling innovation while also protecting customers from bad activity can be tough, but that is exactly what we're striving to do.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
13/ What we can promise:
 
âœ…Weâ€™ll keep listening to you, keep looking for ways to improve, and keep holding ourselves to the highest standards.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
12/ We will continue to strengthen our policies and detection techniques over time:
 
We're adding new forensic tools to better prevent front-running, while also ensuring that we can move more quickly to de-list assets that appear to be run by bad actors.

name: Coinbase
tweet: 11/ We also prohibit employees and contractors from trading crypto assets on material non-public information, such as when a new asset will be added to our platform.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
10/ Investing even more in screening assets and detecting potential front-running:
 
Our first priority is protecting our customers. Thatâ€™s why we have a dedicated team of people screening assets to make sure they meet basic standards, and why we have a trading policy in place.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
9/ Building asset ratings and reviews:
 
Coinbase already provides basic information about each asset so customers can make informed decisions. Weâ€™re going to take it up a level by launching asset ratings and reviews so the community can share additional information on assets.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
8/ Labeling newer and less proven assets on the platform:
 
Some assets are suitable only for more advanced traders, and we want to make sure customers know the potential risk involved. Weâ€™ll continue to develop labels and features that provide clarity for our customers.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
7/ Coinbase strives to be the most trusted crypto exchange in the world. But to maintain that trust, we must always act in the best interests of our customers.
 
Thatâ€™s why today, we want to share some changes we plan to implement over the next few quarters.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
6/ We are always monitoring for situations where a Coinbase employee could, wittingly or unwittingly, leak information to outsiders engaging in illegal activity.
 
We have zero tolerance for this and wonâ€™t hesitate to take action if this activity is identified.

name: Coinbase
tweet: 5/ Going forward, we plan to publish externally once a decision has been made to list an asset, but before any technical integration work begins, to eliminate this category of leaks.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
4/ We are aware of concerns that some market participants may be taking advantage of info leaks in our listings process.
 
Examples: Using blockchain explorer data or using differences in Coinbase API responses to detect when assets might be configured, but not yet launched.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
3/ As a result, we end up listing many ERC-20 assets quickly, while some other assets take longer to review and list.

To some, this looks like weâ€™re playing favorites. In reality, we review assets as quickly as possible.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
2/ We owe it to you to ensure every asset listed on Coinbase meets a set of legal, compliance, and security standards.

Reviewing assets is rigorous and assets built on new chains are technically complex to support.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
1/ At @coinbase, our goal is â€‹â€‹to list every asset that is legal and safe to list.

Pillar 4: Promote Interoperability and Fair Competition

MDAs must be interoperable with products and services across the cryptoeconomy. If fully realized, this can enshrine fair competition, responsible innovation, and promote a thriving dev ecosystem.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
Pillar 2: Designate One Regulator for Digital Asset Markets

Responsibility should be assigned to a single federal regulator and a new registration process established for MDAs. A dedicated self-regulatory organization should also be established. 

Together they set rules.

name: Coinbase
tweet:
Pillar 1: Regulate Digital Assets Under a New Framework

Our existing financial regulatory system doesn't work for the decentralized networks crypto has created. A new framework for digital assets will ensure that innovation will not be hampered by a transition from old ways.

name: Coinbase
tweet: Economies can sometimes prosper as money supply grows from independent central banking. On the other hand, economic history is fraught with hyperinflation events, whereby money supply overwhelms demand.

name: Coinbase
tweet: So what gives gold or bitcoin value, in a world without pegged exchange rates? Valuation requires comparing one asset to another with varying volatility. The same holds true for fiat money itself, especially as central banks increase or (rarely) contract money supply.

name: Coinbase
tweet: Compared to gold, Bitcoin is significantly more volatile. However, BTC volatility is dampening over the years. According to @coinmetrics, avg. 180d volatility has declined over the past decade: from 6.4% (2010-2015) down to 3.7% (2015-2020).

name: Coinbase
tweet: Demand is as important as supply, and stock to flow forecasts for price will certainly fail if bitcoin does not possess useful qualities beyond supply scarcity. Not to mention, quantitative forecasts will falter in the reality of obstacles such as bitcoin volatility. https://t.co/n3b1S06Cdp

name: Coinbase
tweet: Full nodes can verify that in May 2020, Bitcoin supply issuance will drop to a rate of ~1.7% annually. A term known as stock to flow (or â€œS2Fâ€) also measures new supply rate over total supply. After the Halving, Bitcoinâ€™s scarcity as measured by S2F will be on par with goldâ€™s.

name: Coinbase
tweet: To independently verify the validity of Bitcoin transactions, anyone in the world can run a full node. Currently, there are over 52k nodes operating in 96 countries verifying Bitcoin. https://t.co/k1FvrWaili

name: Coinbase
tweet: Mining ensures that Bitcoin maintains advantages over gold. No one knows with perfect certainty how much gold exists above ground; there is no way to independently verify the gold supply. With Bitcoin, anyone with even the simplest computer can verify all bitcoin in existence.

name: Coinbase
tweet: Despite two Halvings in the past that limited mining rewards, mining power (hashrate) has recently reached all time highs. Mining plays a critical role in Bitcoin security. As total supply edges toward 21M, network security (hashrate) has increased in parallel. https://t.co/WbxFuzPfBS

name: Coinbase
tweet: Bitcoin has precisely a max supply of 21 million coins, with ~18 million existing currently. Nearly every ten mins, 12.5 new bitcoins are minted as a reward for miners. After May 2020, in an event called the â€œHalvingâ€, mining rewards will cut in half to 6.25.

name: Coinbase

name: Coinbase
